Goal: All game needs an objective;
Rules: How player can interact with environment;
Core loop: Repeated movements that a player can do; 
Feedback: The return the player receives after a core loop;
Flow: The feedback will mantaining the player engagement, for example evolution of character;
Balance: To mantain the engage the game can not be to easy, boring, or to hard, not good to play;
Reward: How the player interact with game can bring consequences creating tension on the decisions;
Meaning: All this interaction needs to creating a different experiences like a deep conection;
Immersion: Making player feel trully party of the game;
Fun: With all of this, remember, games need to be fun, can be competitive, explore, solve puzzles;
